##Why did I stock 300,000 masks this Spring Festival

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

I thought, first to the hospital in Wuhan, Wuhan Safe National Security; then to the hospitals around, doctors safe, we are safe. Otherwise, we won't be able to use our masks.

Dictation, pictures | Zhou Chaoen

Ohauncey ohauncey

I was born in Ningbo in the 1980s, and I graduated from the Zhejiang University in 2003, the year SARS broke out. SARS didn't affect me that much, and that year I found a job in the mobile phone industry in Minhang District, Shanghai.

I founded Shanghai Aiqi Information Technology Co. , Ltd. in 2009, mainly do mobile video, video recording and p-related APPS. Among them, the LEXIU video editor, has 500 million users worldwide. After graduating from university for 17 years, I have been working and living in Shanghai, where I have a family and a career. My Wife, Zhang Li, is a Sichuan girl who also studies computer science. Minhang District is like a second home for us, so to speak.

100,000 deposit for face mask before Wuhan's closure

According to the usual practice, our company will have a holiday on December twenty-nine. On January 22, twenty-eight, a colleague complained to me, the general manager, that it was difficult to buy masks outside. Just two days earlier, on Jan. 20, Zhong Nanshan had said on television that the COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan had been passed from person to person, so fellow survivors began buying masks. Pharmacies are sold out, e-commerce does not ship... I think, in such an international metropolis as Shanghai, it is so difficult to buy masks, it is estimated that other places are even more difficult.

When I got home that day, I told my wife about it. The more we talked, the more we realized that things weren't going well and that something had to be done. Wuhan announced the closure of the city the next day (January 23) . We were worried about the shortage of masks the night before, so we decided to order a batch of masks to be donated to Wuhan.

As the New Year is coming, most of the mask factories are closed. Our company is located in the Xinzhuang, Shanghai Industrial Zone, Shenmin International Student Pioneer Park. Our teacher Xu Hua from the Hattori Department was very helpful in introducing Shengxin (Shanghai) Textile Technology Co. , Ltd. in the industrial zone of Zhangyan town, Jinshan District. The General Manager of the company was hesitant to work overtime to produce masks over the new year, but without orders, he did not dare to leave workers. I'll call them right now and place a deposit of $100,000 for 300,000 masks. They heard that we were sending masks to the hospital and offered us a cost price.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 24th, on the eve of the Lunar New Year, the factory began to work overtime to produce masks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
300,000 masks donated to those most in need in Hubei and Shanghai

At the same time as the factory stepped up production, my wife and I called hospitals in Wuhan based on the information on the Internet. The Internet is full of information these days, not necessarily accurate, we went to the local colleagues and friends in Wuhan, finally contacted the Hubei Provincial Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine in Wuhan, and where director Zhao interface mask.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At that time a lot of express have stopped, although some express companies have the rescue line for the pneumonia epidemic, but the telephone is too busy to call in, we simply paid the courier fee to send directly. On January 25, the first batch of 40 boxes containing 80,000 masks was sent from Shanghai. Doctors in Wuhan used the masks on the second day of the Lunar New Year.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Thanks in many ways to the fast delivery, the volunteers came to Jinshan District on the first day of the New Year to help out, as if it meant more to everyone.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Friends from the Wuhan University, Overseas Chinese, and so on, have also done a lot. After the first masks arrived in Wuhan, doctors in the city volunteered to introduce us to doctors from Jingmen, Huanggang, Xiangyang and other places where supplies were even scarcer.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
With Shengxin's production capacity requisitioned by the Shanghai Economic and Credit Commission on January 26, the factory has no spare capacity to produce masks for us, so we are more cautious about how we distribute the masks on hand.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In order to ensure that masks can be sent to the most needed places, my wife and I together to screen the number of hospitals and docking, Wechat added a lot of hospital doctors group. Are Friends to know, or doctors to refer doctors, to understand the situation is really urgent, we just send. We have to follow up with the delivery of the masks, and we have to be busy until 1:00 am every day.

I started with tens of thousands in a hospital, then 10,000 in a hospital, then 2,000 in a hospital. At first I thought 300,000 masks was a lot, but then I realized it wasn't enough.

I heard that local hospitals in Shanghai were also nervous about masks, so I contacted my wife at the Minhang hospital affiliated to Fudan University in Minhang District and the Shanghai Fifth People's Hospital, and sent 10,000 masks to them. We also heard that workers checking body temperature on highways also lacked face masks, and sent 2,000 more to the Shanghai Municipal Transportation Bureau.

I went back to my hometown in Ningbo for the New Year, and I came back soon. I spent most of the time in Shanghai, and I was busy donating masks. Meanwhile, some relatives and friends who couldn't buy masks came to me asking for them. I just told them that my mask was issued directly to the hospital by the factory and I didn't have it. I thought, first to the hospital in Wuhan, Wuhan Safe National Security; then to the hospitals around, doctors safe, we are safe. Otherwise, we won't be able to use our masks.

Now that 300,000 masks have been given away, my wife and I can finally have peace of mind for the New Year.

Finally, I would like to say one more: Go Wuhan! Go Shanghai! Go China!
